              "Description": "The prevention program begins with the design of the systems.  Both the chlorine and sulfur dioxide systems have redundant or backup systems.  In actuality, there is only one way to handle a leak or either system.  That is to shut off and isolate the system and fix the leak.  So this is the way we handle any possible leak.  In additon, the systems are inspected annually for possible weakness.  This was done in 2003 and will be done every three years.  SOP's are in existence for each operation that is required.  These SOP's are reviewed and updated every year. A work order system is in place that notifies us of the items to be checked annually and updated.",
